OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31402
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1777165389
OL,3,CFalklands sovereignty 'not in
OL,4,Cquestion' amid fears over US stance,
OL,5,CNo 10 says
OL,7,FThe email suggests reassessing US
OL,8,Fsupport for the United Kingdom's claim
OL,9,Fto the Falkland Islands, near
OL,10,FArgentina, which are also known as
OL,11,FIslas Malvinas.
OL,13,FBritain and Argentina went to war over
OL,14,Fthe islands on April 2, 1982, with 255
OL,15,FBritish troops, three Falkland
OL,16,FIslanders and 649 Argentinian military
OL,17,Fpersonnel losing their lives in the 74-
OL,18,Fday conflict.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1777165389
OL,3,CFalklands sovereignty 'not in
OL,4,Cquestion' amid fears over US stance,
OL,5,CNo 10 says
OL,7,FAsked about the latest reports, prime
OL,8,Fminister Sir Keir Starmer's official
OL,9,Fspokesman said: "The UK position is
OL,10,Fclear and isn't going to change...
OL,11,FIt's a long-standing one. It's an
OL,12,Funchanged one, and it will remain the
OL,13,Fcase."
OL,15,F"The Falkland Islands have previously
OL,16,Fvoted overwhelmingly in favour of
OL,17,Fremaining a UK overseas territory, and
OL,18,Fwe've always stood behind the
OL,19,Fislanders' right to self-determination
OL,20,Fand the fact that sovereignty rests
OL,21,Fwith the UK," the No 10 spokesman said.
OL,26,@qD@QOUuD@FO]wD@AOU}D@MO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1777165389
OL,3,CFalklands sovereignty 'not in
OL,4,Cquestion' amid fears over US stance,
OL,5,CNo 10 says
OL,7,FAsked if the government was worried by
OL,8,Fthe risk of the US changing its
OL,9,Fposition on the Falklands, the
OL,10,Fspokesman said: "No, and as I say,
OL,11,Fwe've expressed this position
OL,12,Fpreviously, clearly and consistently
OL,13,Fto successive US administrations, and
OL,14,Fnothing is going to change that."
OL,16,FThe prime minister's spokesman was
OL,17,Falso asked if Britain was ready to
OL,18,Fdefend the islands from any threats.
OL,26,@rD@QOUvD@aO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31405
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1777165389
OL,3,CFalklands sovereignty 'not in
OL,4,Cquestion' amid fears over US stance,
OL,5,CNo 10 says
OL,7,F"The question of the Falkland Islands
OL,8,Fand the UK's sovereignty and the
OL,9,Fislanders' right to self-determination
OL,10,Fis not in question, and we've
OL,11,Fexpressed that position clearly and
OL,12,Fconsistently," he said.
OL,14,FPressed further if the UK could defend
OL,15,Fthe Falklands, he described the
OL,16,Fquestion as a "hypothetical", adding:
OL,17,F"That is not the situation we are in."
OL,26,@oD@AOUtD@NO]xD@OOUxD@\O]yD@AOUyD@fO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/12
